message.content:
Probabilistic Methods, Rule Learning. 

Probabilistic Methods: The paper discusses the performance improvement of the Naive-Bayes algorithm when features were discretized using an entropy-based method. Naive-Bayes is a probabilistic algorithm that relies on Bayes' theorem to make predictions.

Rule Learning: The paper also discusses the performance improvement of the C4.5 induction algorithm when features were discretized in advance. C4.5 is a rule learning algorithm that builds decision trees based on the discretized features.
